33:14.390 --> 33:18.400
that seldom – Sahaja Yogis are never very
well-off people I mean, to that extent that

33:18.400 --> 33:19.670
you’ll have cars after cars.

33:19.670 --> 33:22.990
I said, “What business do you do all of
you?”

33:22.990 --> 33:26.760
They said, “You see, actually we are all
people growing tobacco."

33:26.760 --> 33:29.110
And I said, “Very nice."

33:29.110 --> 33:32.299
They are growing now, you see, not only eating
but growing also.

33:32.299 --> 33:34.820
And I said…

33:34.820 --> 33:40.570
In their houses you’ll be surprised, they
had tiles made in England, they had taps made

33:40.570 --> 33:41.570
in England.

33:41.570 --> 33:45.309
All these ancient things that you have had
which you treat as antiques today, they all

33:45.309 --> 33:47.190
had everything with them made in England [laughter].

33:47.190 --> 33:48.799
I said, “Made in England.

33:48.799 --> 33:49.799
How do you get all these things in here?”

33:49.799 --> 33:54.110
The things you do not have here they had it
there.

33:54.110 --> 33:56.280
I said, “How did you get it?”

33:56.280 --> 33:57.900
He said, “We are exporting tobacco to England."

33:57.900 --> 34:06.059
I said, “Very nice, what a nice work you
